## Lodge Life and Activities

There were only 17 of us guests in this intimate lodge, immediately bonded by a love of nature and wildlife. Over the next five days, we enjoyed:  

- **Two daily hikes/walks** in soggy tundra, muck, or rocks, searching for bears or learning about the ecosystem.  
- **Three hearty, healthy meals** a day.  
- **Evening lectures**.  
- Continuous monitoring from the **watchtower**, either by staff or zealous guests like my daughter.  

Weather varied: we occasionally had T-shirt weather, but also stood in frigid rain one morning to admire a mom with two youngsters and a solo bear, all out on a spit. (The threesome were the same bears who greeted us upon arrival and saw us off when we left.)

### Beluga Day

One day was devoted to belugas. We took **Zodiacs** out on Hudson Bay where belugas swam all around us (and yes, a polar bear was swimming too!).

